app.cards.game

Class FullHouse

  • java.lang.Object
    • app.cards.game.FullHouse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HandValue, java.lang.Comparable<FullHouse>

    public class FullHouse
extends java.lang.Object
implements HandValue, java.lang.Comparable<FullHouse>

    This class encapsulates a three of a kind and a pair that together make a full house.

    A FullHouse instance is created via makeBestFullHouse(List) from a sorted List of NOfAKinds.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(FullHouse other)

        Compares this FullHouse to another

        A full house f1 is better than a full house f2 if its three of a kind is better. If the three of a kinds of both full houses are equal, the full house with the better pair wins.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<FullHouse>
        Returns:
        A negative number if other is better than this FullHouse, a positive number if this FullHouse is better than other, 0 if they're equal
